parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, breakdown, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leaks
water pump failure
thermostat failure
head gasket failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the oil filter housing can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, breakdown, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks
oil filter housing failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system when braking can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering locks or binds when applying the brakes at low speeds
the steering gets stiff when backing and turning
the steering feels heavy or difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake master cylinder leaks fluid
the front brakes wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle feels as if it has lifted off the ground
pulls violently to one side
fumes and smoke are coming from the wheels
excessive brake wear
premature need for new brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: The vehicle is using 2 or more quarts of oil per week.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alignment issues can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and affect the vehicle's handling, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle is out of alignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A/C compressor failure can cause discomfort to the driver and passengers, and potentially lead to overheating.
symptoms: The A/C compressor makes a noise as if it were a bad pulley bearing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The center console is broken
the crew cab outside lights never worked
the wipers failed during a rain storm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear end failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The rear end leaked
the rear end wheel separated about two inches out of position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage or failure, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: The water pump was inoperative
the radiator exploded sending anti-freeze all over the engine.
